:INFO
Parts List for a DIY Electric Longboard
Full parts list with specs for a dual hub motor electric longboard build targeting 25 kph top speed and 15 km range.

:TASK
[ ] 38 to 42 inch drop-through longboard deck
[ ] 218mm longboard trucks two pairs
[ ] Dual 90mm hub motors 6374 or equivalent with matching wheels
[ ] VESC 4.12 or Flipsky FSESC speed controller
[ ] 10S2P or 12S2P lithium ion battery pack with BMS
[ ] Hoyt St or Flipsky VX1 handheld remote with receiver
[ ] XT90S antispark connectors for battery main lead
[ ] Power switch with pre-charge resistor for ESC protection
[ ] 3D printed or CNC aluminum enclosure for electronics
[ ] M3 and M4 stainless hardware for motor and enclosure mounts
[ ] Heat shrink tubing and silicone wire 12AWG for motor phase leads

:NOTE
Order spare inner tubes for hub motor wheels. The inner tubes are proprietary to each hub motor brand and hard to source locally. Carry a spare on long rides until you know your board's reliability.

